definition.value: A glycosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of a xylose and, by extension, of a lower oligosaccharide having xylose at the reducing end.
The fucosyl group of alpha-L configuration. A proposed epitope of blood group O antigen.
A 1,2-diacyl-3-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are oleoyl and palmitoyl respectively.
A 2,3-diacyl-1-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 2- and 3-positions are both palmitoyl.
A class of galactoglycerolipids that consists of 1-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol having unspecified acyl groups attached at position 2 and 3.
A 2,3-diacyl-1-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 2- and 3-positions are both oleoyl.
A 2,3-diacyl-1-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are palmitoyl and oleoyl respectively.
A carboxylic ester derivative of chloroamphenicol incorporating an L-lysino group linked via a 2-oxoethyl group to the oxygen at C-3.
A 1,2-diacyl-3-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are both stearoyl.
A 1,2-diacyl-3-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are stearoyl and palmitoyl respectively.
A 1-acyl-3-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol where the 1-acyl group is specified as palmitoyl.

A hydroxy-1,4-naphthoquinone that is 1,4-naphthoquinone substituted by hydroxy and 3-methylbut-2-en-1-yl groups at positions 2 and 3, respectively. It is a natural compound that exhibits antibacterial and anticancer properties, first isolated in 1882 from the bark of Tabebuia avellanedae.

A sulfonamide that is a 3-methoxypyrazin-2-yl derivative of (E)-N-(4-(N-(4,6-dimethylpyrimidin-2-yl)sulfamoyl)phenyl)-3-(5-nitrothiophene-2-yl)acrylamide. Necrosulfonamide specifically blocks necrosis downstream of the activation of RIP3 (the receptor-interacting serine-threonine kinase 3), a key signalling molecule in the programmed necrosis (necroptosis) pathway.
A class of galactoglycerolipids that consists of any 1-acyl-sn-glycerol having an alpha-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3.
A 1-acyl-3-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol where the 1-acyl group is specified as oleoyl.
A carbamoyl derivative of butyric acid which includes a 1,3-diketone functionality.
A 1,2-diacyl-3-beta-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are both palmitoyl.
A 1,2-diacyl-3-beta-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are both oleoyl.
An alpha-amino fatty acid of chain length C16.
A glycopeptide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 6-O-butyrylated muramyl dipeptide with the hydroxy group of N-hydroxy-5-norbornene-2,3-dicarboxylmide.
A CMP-sugar having pseudaminic acid as the sugar component.
A glycosylglycerol derivative in which the glycosyl moiety is alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-glucosyl attached at O-3, with O-1 and O-2 both acylated.
Traseolide in (S,S)-trans configuration.

An indane derivative in which the indane skeleton is substituted by geminal methyl groups at C-1, by single methyl groups at C-2 and C-6, by an isopropyl group at C-3 and by an acetyl group at C-6.  It is a constituent of musk odorant.
A glycosylglycerol derivative in which the glycosyl moiety is alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-glucosyl attached at O-3, with O-1 and O-2 both acylated.

An indane derivative in which the indane skeleton is substituted by geminal methyl groups at C-1, by a single methyl group at C-6, by an isopropyl group at C-3 and by a 3-carboxypropanoyl group at C-6.

A glycosylglycerol derivative in which the glycosyl moiety is alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-glucosyl attached at O-3, with O-1 and O-2 both acylated.
A glycosylglycerol derivative in which the glycosyl moiety is D-glucosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-glucosyl attached at O-3, with O-1 and O-2 both acylated.
A glycosylglycerol derivative in which the glycosyl moiety is beta-D-glucosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucosyl attached at O-3, with O-1 and O-2 both acylated.

An indane derivative in which the indane skeleton is substituted by an ethyl group at C-2, geminal methyl groups at C-1, by a single methyl group at C-6, by an isopropyl group at C-3 and by a 3-carboxypropanoyl group at C-6.
A glycosylglycerol derivative in which the glycosyl moiety is alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-glucosyl attached at O-3, with O-1 and O-2 both acylated.
An N-acyl-L-homoserine lactone having 3-oxohexanoyl as the acyl substituent.
The amino-acid anion formed by proton loss from the carboxylic acid function of a glyco-amino acid.
A dicarboximide that consists of 1-oxoisoindoline bearing an amino substituent at position 4 and a 2,6-dioxopiperidin-3-yl group at position 2. Inhibits the secretion of TNF-alpha.
A 7-deazaguanine ribonucleoside obtained by formal epoxidation of the cyclohexene moiety of queuosine.
An agonist that selectively binds to and activates a retinoid X receptor.
A retinoid that consists of all-trans-retinoic acid bearing a hydroxy substituent at position 4 on the cyclohexenyl ring.
A tricarboxylic acid trianion obtained by deprotonation of the three carboxy groups of N(alpha)-citryl-N(epsilon)-acetyl-N(epsilon)-hydroxylysine.
A monohydroxybenzoate that is the conjugate base of 3-hydroxy-4-methoxybenzoic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A methoxybenzoic acid that is 4-methoxybenzoic acid bearing a hydroxy substituent at position 3.
A urea that consists of 1-butylurea having a 4-hydroxymethylbenzenesulfonyl group attached at the 3-position.
An isoquinoline that is 3,4-dihydroisoquinoline bearing amidino and hydroxy substituent at positions 2 and 4 respectively.
An L-lysine derivative that is N(alpha)-citryl-L-lysine having hydroxy and acetyl substituents attached to the side-chain amino group.
A retinoid that consists of 9-cis-retinoic acid bearing a hydroxy substituent at position 4 on the cyclohexenyl ring.
A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (E)-2,3-didehydropristanic acid.
A imidazolidine-2,4-dione that consists of hydantoin bearing phenyl and 4-hydroxyphenyl substituents at position 5.

A linear heptasaccharide glycosyl group consisisting of one iduronic acid residue sulfated on O-2, two glucosamine residues, both sulfated on nitrogen and with one also sulfated at O-3 and the other sulfated at O-6, one glucuronic acid residue, and two galactose residues linked to a xylosyl residue at the reducing end and which is commonly bonded to an amino acid residue.
